	wordHeading={`God's words are a treasure`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>When you read God's Word, something wonderful happens inside you. His words are like little seeds that grow love and peace and joy in your heart. Even if you don't understand every word yet, God's words never stop working. They make you strong and happy, deep down.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"Your word is like a lamp that shows me the way." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Psalm 119:105</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says to you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"Hello, My child. I am your Father in heaven, and I want you to know something very important. I made you. I picked your smile and your laugh. When you were so tiny that nobody could see you yet, I already knew your name. And I already loved you.</p><p>You don't have to be the best at anything for Me to love you. You don't have to be perfect. You don't have to win. I love you when you do great, and I love you just the same when you make a mistake. My love for you never, ever gets smaller.</p><p>So when you are scared, talk to Me — I am right here. When you are sad, I am close. When you are happy, I am happy too. I am awake all night while you sleep, watching over you. You are My child, and I am so glad you are Mine. I love you so much."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for children`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for these children. Let them hear Your whisper above every loud or scary thing — the worries, the comparing, the voices that make them feel small. Let them encounter Your love — not as a rule, but as a Father's delight — and know they are Your beloved, apart from being the best or the smartest or the fastest.</p><p>Give them grace to receive who they are from You before the world tries to tell them who to be. Father, wrap Your arms around every child who feels scared or sad or left out tonight, and let them feel how close You are. I pray Your protection over them from the enemy, from temptation, from anything that would harm or frighten them, and from despair.</p><p>Let them know there is no condemnation in You, that they are fearfully and wonderfully made, and that nothing can separate them from Your love. Let them know You, their Father, as their true home and their safest place. And may they wake up every single day knowing they are loved by their heavenly Father.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
