	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for children about God's love?`, answer: `Psalm 139:14 (you are wonderfully made), Mark 10:14 (Jesus says let the children come to Me), Matthew 10:30-31 (God knows the hairs on your head), Isaiah 41:10 (do not be afraid, I am with you), John 1:12 (you can be a child of God), Psalm 23:1 (the Lord is my shepherd), and 1 John 3:1 (see how much the Father loves us) all speak gently to children. You can read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say to a child who feels scared?`, answer: `The Bible says you are not alone. In Isaiah 41:10 your Father says, "Do not be afraid, because I am with you… I will hold you up with My strong right hand." Jesus promises in John 14 that He will never leave you. When a child feels scared, they can talk to God like talking to the kindest dad in the world — and He always listens. Read these verses free with audio in the Father's Heart Bible™.` },
		{ question: `How can I read the Bible with my young child?`, answer: `The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online, with warm, simple words and audio on every chapter — so you can read it together, or play it at bedtime. Many families start with short, comforting passages like Psalm 23, Psalm 139, or the stories of Jesus blessing the children in Mark 10. No account, no purchase, and no app needed — just open fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Does the Bible say God loves children?`, answer: `Yes, very much. Jesus said, "Let the little children come to Me" (Mark 10:14), and 1 John 3:1 says, "See how much the Father loves us! His love is so great that we are called children of God." The whole Bible shows a Father who made each child on purpose, knows their name, and delights in them. The Father's Heart Bible™ makes that love easy for kids to hear and understand.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free online Bible with audio for kids?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on any phone, tablet, or computer and play the audio while you read along. It's gentle and simple enough for a grown-up to read with a young child, or for an older child to enjoy on their own.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ good for children?`, answer: `It reveals God as a loving Father — a good, kind Dad — wherever the Bible reveals Him that way. For a child, that changes everything: instead of a faraway, scary God, they meet a Father who made them, knows their name, and is never too busy. The warm words and free audio make it easy and comforting for kids to read or hear, especially at bedtime.` },
		{ question: `What Bible verse helps a child fall asleep feeling safe?`, answer: `Psalm 23:1 ("The Father is my shepherd; He takes care of me") and Zephaniah 3:17 (God "will even sing happy songs because of you") are gentle bedtime verses. So is Psalm 139, which says God made you in an amazing and wonderful way. Playing these passages on the free Father's Heart Bible™ audio at fathersheartbible.com/read can help a child fall asleep knowing their Father is watching over them.` },
